The paper focuses on providing a comprehensive security plan for smaller enterprises with limited resources, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses best practices for authentication, authorization, auditing, firewall, intrusion detection, and prevention, which are all related to software engineering (cs.SE), network infrastructure (cs.NI), cybersecurity (cs.CY), and systems and information theory (cs.SI).
